1. Passenger Class
Description: Represents a passenger using the Tap and Pay system.
Attributes:
passengerID: int – Unique ID for each passenger
name: String – Full name of passenger
email: String – Email address
phoneNumber: String – Contact number
walletBalance: float – Current digital wallet balance
transactionHistory: List<Transaction> – List of past transactions
Methods:
register() – Register a new passenger account
login() – Authenticate passenger
linkWallet(accountDetails) – Link bank or wallet
tapToPay(fareAmount) – Make a payment
viewTransactionHistory() – Display past transactions
updateProfile(details) – Update passenger information
2. BusConductor Class
Description: Represents a conductor who verifies payments.
Attributes:
conductorID: int – Unique ID for conductor
name: String – Conductor name
assignedBusID: int – Bus assigned to conductor
Methods:
verifyPayment(passengerID) – Check passenger payment status
displayBoardingStatus(passengerID) – Show if passenger is allowed to board
3. BusDriver Class
Description: Represents the driver of the bus.
Attributes:
driverID: int – Unique driver ID
name: String – Driver name
busID: int – Bus assigned to driver
Methods:
monitorBoarding() – Observe boarding flow
alertConductor(issue) – Report issues to conductor
4. Admin / TransportAuthority Class
Description: Represents admin for monitoring and reporting.
Attributes:
adminID: int – Unique admin ID
name: String – Admin name
role: String – Admin role (reporting, monitoring)
Methods:
generateReport(type) – Generate daily/weekly/monthly reports
monitorSystem() – Track system and device status
manageUsers(userID, action) – Add/update/delete users
performMaintenance() – Execute system updates
5. PaymentGateway Class
Description: Represents external payment gateway for processing payments.
Attributes:
gatewayID: int – Unique gateway identifier
name: String – Gateway name
transactionLog: List<Transaction> – Log of processed transactions
Methods:
processPayment(amount, passengerID) – Authorize and deduct payment
validateAccount(accountDetails) – Verify bank or wallet accounts
sendConfirmation(transactionID) – Notify system of transaction result
6. Transaction Class
Description: Represents a single payment transaction.
Attributes:
transactionID: int – Unique transaction ID
passengerID: int – Passenger associated with transaction
amount: float – Fare amount
status: String – Payment status (Success/Failure)
timestamp: DateTime – Date and time of transaction
Methods:
logTransaction() – Record transaction in system
updateStatus(status) – Update payment status
